Package RaccoonRush.util

Record Class Config

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
RaccoonRush.util.Config
Record Components:
originalTileSize - The original size of the tile.
scale - The scale factor for the game.
maxScreenCol - The maximum number of columns on the screen.
maxScreenRow - The maximum number of rows on the screen.
maxWorldCol - The maximum number of columns in the world.
maxWorldRow - The maximum number of rows in the world.
FPS - The frames per second for the game.
animationFPS - The frames per second for animations.
playerSpeed - The speed of the player.
enemySpeed - The speed of enemies.
public record Config(int originalTileSize, int scale, int maxScreenCol, int maxScreenRow, int maxWorldCol, int maxWorldRow, int FPS, int animationFPS, int playerSpeed, int enemySpeed, int enemyDamage, Move entityDirection) extends Record
This record represents the configuration for the game. It is a compact form of class that holds immutable data. The fields include originalTileSize, scale, maxScreenCol, maxScreenRow, maxWorldCol, maxWorldRow, and FPS. The record automatically generates public final fields and accessors for the data, as well as appropriate implementations of equals(), hashCode(), and toString().
